review:
An alright puzzle game with 96 levels to solve in either normal or timed mode. Personally I wasn't really a fan of the timed mode but if you are not a completionist you can just happily skip it as the timed levels just seem to be mirrored normal levels for what I can tell. Normal mode was enjoyable however. At the beginning I was worried the game would be extremely easy but the difficulty did go up after a while.

There is a few things I found missing:
- dark mode doesn't work;
- an undo button so if you mess up just a tiny bit you don't need to redo the whole path again;
- would be nice to have a keyboard bind to reset the whole puzzle would have been especially nice for the timed levels.

Works without any issues on Linux with Proton (7.0-6).

